EXCEPT SOME PULL-UPS.

23:21.483 --> 23:23.652
UGH, UGH,
UGH, UGH. WHOO.

23:23.735 --> 23:24.986
NOW WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO DO?

23:28.949 --> 23:31.076
{\an1}OK, COSMO AND WANDA
MIGHT BE GONE,

23:31.159 --> 23:32.452
BUT EVERYTHING'S GREAT!

23:32.536 --> 23:35.122
{\an8}AFTER ALL,
I'M THE PRESIDENT!

23:35.205 --> 23:37.207
AND I GET ALL THESE FREE PENS!

23:39.126 --> 23:40.168
[GROWLING]

23:40.252 --> 23:41.253
YOU!

23:42.003 --> 23:45.298
THAT'S RIGHT,
PRESIDENT TURNER.

23:45.382 --> 23:47.843
AH, CIRCUS PEANUTS!

23:47.926 --> 23:49.678
THAT'S RIGHT. IT'S ME!

23:49.761 --> 23:51.555
{\an1}DID YOU REALLY THINK
YOU'D BE ABLE TO GET AWAY

23:51.638 --> 23:52.347
WITH SENDING
YOUR KID ARMIES

23:52.430 --> 23:54.391
TO DESTROY
CAMP LEARN-A-TORIUM?

23:54.474 --> 23:57.310
YEAH! THAT'S WHY
WE TORE IT DOWN!

23:59.729 --> 24:00.647
{\an1}AND HERE'S
A COMMEMORATIVE PEN

24:00.730 --> 24:03.442
FROM THE BILL I SIGNED
ENDORSING THE ACTION.

24:03.525 --> 24:05.861
HEY, THANKS.
I--OOH, DARN IT!

24:05.944 --> 24:06.528
THAT PLACE WAS GREAT!

24:06.611 --> 24:08.530
{\an1}DUDE, THAT PLACE
WAS LAME!

24:08.613 --> 24:09.489
[GASPING]

24:09.573 --> 24:10.824
IT CAN'T BE LAME.

24:13.118 --> 24:15.954
{\an1}EVERYTHING I KNEW ABOUT FUN
WENT INTO THAT PLACE.

24:16.037 --> 24:18.456
[LAUGHING]

24:19.958 --> 24:20.333
[GASPING]

24:20.417 --> 24:22.127
OH, CONFETTI!

24:22.210 --> 24:23.837
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

24:23.920 --> 24:26.006
NO. THAT WAS FUN!

24:26.089 --> 24:28.008
{\an1}YOU SHOULD DO
MORE STUFF LIKE THAT!

24:28.091 --> 24:29.092
I WAS TAUGHT
THAT BORING WAS FUN,

24:29.176 --> 24:31.803
THAT DULL WAS FUN.

24:31.887 --> 24:32.846
WHO WOULD TELL YOU

24:32.929 --> 24:34.347
{\an1}THAT DULL AND BORING
WAS FUN?

24:36.099 --> 24:38.393
HELLO, SON.

24:38.476 --> 24:39.561
[GASPING]

24:39.644 --> 24:41.062
{\an1}WHAT THE HECK
IS GOING ON HERE?

24:41.146 --> 24:43.523
MONTAGE, PLEASE.

24:43.607 --> 24:44.816
[RINGING]

24:47.319 --> 24:49.613
H.P.: SINCE THE DAYS
WE FOUND HIM

24:49.696 --> 24:52.282
IN THE UNTAMED WILDS OF KANSAS,

24:52.365 --> 24:55.577
{\an1}WE HAVE BEEN SECRETLY
WATCHING OVER FLAPPY BOB.

24:57.871 --> 24:59.789
WHETHER IT WAS AS A BABY...

25:01.082 --> 25:02.459
[RINGING]

25:07.130 --> 25:10.842
OR AS A YOUNG MAN...

25:15.931 --> 25:17.807
UGH!

25:20.852 --> 25:25.148
WE ALWAYS DELIVERED
OUR SPECIAL BRAND OF CARE-GIVING

25:25.232 --> 25:27.609
TO SEE THAT FLAPPY
WAS TAKEN CARE OF.

25:29.486 --> 25:30.820
EVEN IF HE DIDN'T KNOW HOW.

25:34.866 --> 25:36.534
AH!

25:43.541 --> 25:45.460
WE MADE SURE HE HAD
EVERYTHING HE NEEDED

25:45.543 --> 25:47.879
{\an1}TO LIVE OUR--
I MEAN, HIS DREAM.

25:52.467 --> 25:55.220
LEARN-A-TORIUM!

25:58.640 --> 26:03.311
{\an1}A 37-YEAR-LONG DREAM
YOU DESTROYED, TURNER.

26:03.395 --> 26:05.647
{\an1}YEAH, HE DID
DESTROY MY DREAM!

26:05.730 --> 26:06.815
{\an1}SO, WHO ARE YOU,
ANYWAY?

26:06.898 --> 26:08.400
{\an1}LONG-LOST COUSINS?
DISTANT UNCLES? WHAT?

26:08.483 --> 26:11.069
{\an1}AND WHAT'S
WITH THE FLOATING?

26:11.152 --> 26:13.238
{\an1}WE HAVE THAT KIND
OF MONEY.

26:13.321 --> 26:15.490
WALKING IS
FOR POOR PEOPLE.

26:15.573 --> 26:16.157
WE LIKE TO
THINK OF OURSELVES

26:16.241 --> 26:18.159
AS YOUR GODPARENTS.

26:18.243 --> 26:20.704
GODPARENTS? OH, NO!

26:20.787 --> 26:21.371
THAT MEANS THEY
CAN GRANT A WISH!

26:21.454 --> 26:23.957
GODPARENTS
WITH THE MONEY

26:24.040 --> 26:25.959
TO GIVE YOU
ANYTHING YOU WANT

26:26.042 --> 26:28.336
IF YOU JUST
SIGN HERE.

26:28.420 --> 26:29.879
AS PART OF THE CONTRACT,

26:29.963 --> 26:33.174
{\an1}YOU GET TO MAKE THE WORLD
EXACTLY THE WAY YOU WANT TO,

26:33.258 --> 26:34.259
AND ALL WE WANT IN RETURN

26:34.342 --> 26:38.013
ARE CERTAIN MERCHANDISING
RIGHTS, A FEW ROYALTIES,

26:38.096 --> 26:40.890
{\an1}AND ABSOLUTE CONTROL
OF FAIRY WORLD.

26:43.435 --> 26:44.436
OH, MY GOSH!

26:44.519 --> 26:45.520
I KNOW WHAT
THEY'RE UP TO!

26:45.603 --> 26:47.689
NO! YOU HAVE TO
LISTEN TO ME!

26:47.772 --> 26:48.940
I KNOW THEY'RE THE GUYS

26:49.024 --> 26:50.775
{\an5}WHO'VE GIVEN YOU
EVERYTHING YOU'VE
EVER WANTED,

26:50.859 --> 26:51.943
AND I'M JUST THE GUY

26:52.027 --> 26:52.736
WHO DESTROYED
YOUR LIFELONG DREAM,

26:52.819 --> 26:55.572
BUT YOU HAVE TO
LISTEN TO ME!

26:55.655 --> 26:56.906
BOY, THAT
CAME OUT WRONG.

26:56.990 --> 26:58.742
BUT I GAVE YOU
THE PEN!

26:58.825 --> 27:00.076
FORGET IT, KID.

27:00.160 --> 27:01.870
{\an1}I KNOW
WHO MY FRIENDS ARE,

27:01.953 --> 27:03.121
AND I'M SIGNING
THAT CONTRACT!

27:03.204 --> 27:05.540
WAIT!

27:05.623 --> 27:07.834
{\an1}♪ FLAPPY BOB, CAN'T YOU SEE
WHAT THEY'VE DONE? ♪

27:10.587 --> 27:13.715
♪ THEY NEEDED A PAWN,
AND CLEARLY YOU WERE THE ONE ♪

27:13.798 --> 27:17.177
{\an1}♪ THEY TOOK AWAY
YOUR CLOWNY CLOTHES ♪

27:17.260 --> 27:20.221
♪ YOUR FLOPPY SHOES
AND BIG RED NOSE ♪

27:20.305 --> 27:21.514
♪ JUST LOOK AROUND ♪

27:21.598 --> 27:23.933
{\an1}♪ HOW COULD YOU SAY
THIS IS FUN? ♪

27:29.147 --> 27:32.609
{\an1}♪ SINCE YOU WERE BORN,
THEY DECIDED YOUR FATE ♪

27:34.361 --> 27:38.448
{\an1}♪ FROM THE STYLE OF YOUR CAR
DOWN TO THE FOOD THAT YOU ATE ♪

27:38.531 --> 27:40.742
♪ I KNOW IT SEEMS
THEY GAVE A LOT ♪

27:40.825 --> 27:43.912
♪ BUT I'M TELLING YOU
IT'S PART OF A PLOT ♪

27:43.995 --> 27:45.622
♪ A PLOT THAT YOU CAN STOP ♪

27:45.705 --> 27:47.874
♪ STOP IT BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE ♪

27:50.168 --> 27:51.503
H.P. and Sanderson:
♪ HEY, FLAPPY BOB ♪

27:51.586 --> 27:52.796
{\an1}♪ YOU HEAR WHAT
HE BEEN SPREADING? ♪

27:52.879 --> 27:54.422
♪ THE LIES THAT
HE'S BEEN TELLING ♪

27:54.506 --> 27:55.715
♪ I KNOW WHERE
THIS IS HEADING ♪

27:55.799 --> 27:57.217
♪ TOWARDS TURNING
YOU AGAINST US ♪

27:57.300 --> 27:58.635
{\an5}♪ TO RESENT US ♪

27:57.300 --> 27:58.635
♪ AND PRESENT US ♪

27:58.718 --> 27:59.886
{\an5}♪ AND SUGGEST ♪

27:58.718 --> 27:59.886
♪ WHO ARE THE VILLAINS? ♪

27:59.969 --> 28:00.553
♪ YEAH, DON'T YOU BE
FORGETTING ♪

28:00.637 --> 28:02.847
♪ IT WAS YOU, FLAPPY BOB ♪

28:02.931 --> 28:04.349
♪ YEAH, YOU WERE THE ONE ♪

28:04.432 --> 28:05.475
{\an5}♪ WE PROTECTED ♪

28:04.432 --> 28:05.475
♪ AND RESPECTED ♪

28:05.558 --> 28:07.185
{\an1}♪ AS THOUGH
YOU WERE OUR SON ♪

28:07.268 --> 28:08.061
♪ AND NOW YOU'RE
IN THE MIDDLE ♪

28:08.144 --> 28:09.771
♪ YOU CAN FIDDLE
WITH THIS RIDDLE ♪

28:09.854 --> 28:11.231
{\an1}♪ OR YOU CAN SIGN
THIS DEAL AND TRUST US ♪

28:11.314 --> 28:12.982
{\an1}♪ THAT YOUR WISHES
WILL BE DONE ♪

28:13.066 --> 28:13.650
♪ WHERE IS THE FUN? ♪

28:13.733 --> 28:15.777
♪ WHO SHOULD I TURN TO? ♪

28:15.860 --> 28:17.112
♪ WHERE IS THE FUN? ♪

28:17.195 --> 28:18.530
♪ HOW CAN I LEARN WHO? ♪

28:18.613 --> 28:19.739
♪ WHO IS THE ONE? ♪

28:19.823 --> 28:22.200
{\an1}♪ THE ONE I CAN TRUST
TO TELL ME WHAT'S FUN ♪

28:22.283 --> 28:24.285
[POP]

28:24.369 --> 28:24.994
♪ WHERE IS THE FUN? ♪

28:25.078 --> 28:27.205
♪ WHY SHOULD
I TRUST YOU? ♪

28:27.288 --> 28:28.498
♪ HE WAS THE ONE ♪

28:28.581 --> 28:31.167
♪ YOU WERE THE ONE
WHO WANTED TO SHUN ♪

28:31.251 --> 28:34.170
♪ EVERYTHING I ALWAYS
THOUGHT FUN ♪

28:34.254 --> 28:35.672
{\an1}[RINGING]

28:35.755 --> 28:38.925
{\an1}♪ HEY, FLAPPY BOB,
CAN'T YOU SEE IN YOUR HEART? ♪

28:40.677 --> 28:42.262
♪ THERE'S A ROLE YOU PLAY ♪

28:42.345 --> 28:44.597
♪ AND, DUDE, THIS JUST
AIN'T THE RIGHT PART ♪

28:44.681 --> 28:47.642
{\an1}♪ I KNOW MY ACTIONS
WEREN'T IDEAL ♪

28:47.725 --> 28:50.228
{\an1}♪ BUT HOW DO YOUR
CLOWNY PARENTS FEEL ♪

28:50.311 --> 28:55.150
{\an1}♪ ABOUT THE PATH YOU CHOSE,
WHETHER OR NOT IT WAS SMART? ♪

28:55.233 --> 28:55.817
♪ WHERE IS THE FUN? ♪

28:55.900 --> 28:57.902
♪ WHO SHOULD I TURN TO? ♪

28:57.986 --> 28:58.528
♪ WHERE IS THE FUN? ♪

28:58.611 --> 29:00.864
♪ HOW CAN I LEARN WHO? ♪

29:00.947 --> 29:02.115
♪ WHO IS THE ONE ♪

29:02.198 --> 29:05.368
{\an1}♪ THE ONE I CAN TRUST
TO TELL ME WHAT'S FUN ♪

29:05.452 --> 29:07.662
♪ WHERE IS THE FUN? ♪

29:07.745 --> 29:09.289
♪ I'M SO CONFLICTED ♪

29:09.372 --> 29:09.998
♪ BUT HE WAS THE ONE ♪

29:10.081 --> 29:12.083
♪ THE ONE WHO RESTRICTED ♪

29:12.167 --> 29:13.501
♪ YOUR VISION OF FUN ♪

29:13.585 --> 29:16.504
{\an1}♪ AND WITH THIS PEN
I'LL SIGN BY LINE ITEM 1 ♪

29:16.588 --> 29:17.630
{\an1}NO!

29:17.714 --> 29:21.634
{\an1}♪ MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT,
COULD BE A GIANT MISTAKE ♪

29:21.718 --> 29:23.344
{\an8}[DULL LAUGHING]

29:23.428 --> 29:26.848
♪ BUT CHANGING MY LIFE'S A RISK
I'M NOT READY TO TAKE ♪

29:26.931 --> 29:28.892
♪ THIS NOSE,
PANTS, HAIR, AND SHOES ♪

29:28.975 --> 29:32.228
{\an1}♪ THEY'RE ALL MY PAST,
AND NOW I CHOOSE ♪

29:32.312 --> 29:34.397
♪ TO WISH FOR A WORLD ♪

29:34.481 --> 29:36.524
♪ A WORLD
THAT FITS ALL MY VIEWS ♪

29:38.818 --> 29:40.445
♪ A WORLD WHERE I'M SAFE ♪

29:40.528 --> 29:42.113
IT'S OVER, TURNER.
YOU LOSE!

29:45.325 --> 29:46.326
[RINGING]

29:46.409 --> 29:47.076
THANKS FOR THE PEN.

29:59.589 --> 30:00.465
AAH!

30:00.548 --> 30:01.966
OH, NO!

30:03.343 --> 30:05.303
♪ I'M HAPPY PEPPY DAD ♪

30:05.386 --> 30:07.472
♪ I'M HAPPY PEPPY MOM ♪

30:08.932 --> 30:11.309
NO!

30:14.479 --> 30:16.064
{\an1}Jorgen: DON'T MAKE THIS
ANY MORE PAINFUL

30:16.147 --> 30:16.731
THAN IT HAS TO BE.

30:16.814 --> 30:18.483
ISN'T THERE
SUPPOSED TO BE

30:18.566 --> 30:19.484
A GOOD COP
AND A BAD COP?

30:19.567 --> 30:21.694
WE HAD SOME CUTBACKS.

30:21.778 --> 30:23.696
{\an1}NOW, DO YOU WANT
TO STAY IN FAIRY JAIL

30:23.780 --> 30:26.074
{\an1}FOR THE REST
OF YOUR FAIRY LIFE,

30:26.157 --> 30:28.618
OR DO YOU WANT
TO BLAME COSMO?

30:28.701 --> 30:29.786
NO!

30:29.869 --> 30:32.205
{\an1}PLEASE?

30:32.288 --> 30:33.373
NO!

30:33.456 --> 30:36.584
{\an1}OK. GOOD COP OVER.
BLAME COSMO!

30:36.668 --> 30:37.961
BLAME COSMO?

30:43.174 --> 30:46.219
♪ I WAS LOST TILL HE FOUND ME ♪

30:46.302 --> 30:49.472
♪ AND ALTHOUGH HE CONFOUNDS ME ♪

30:49.556 --> 30:53.268
♪ BY HIS CROWN
IS WHERE I KNOW I SHOULD BE ♪

30:53.351 --> 30:55.645
{\an1}AAH!

30:55.728 --> 30:57.605
♪ YES, I KNOW HE'S A MORON ♪

30:57.689 --> 31:00.942
♪ WITH A BRAIN MADE OF BORON ♪

31:01.025 --> 31:06.197
♪ AND YET I'M DRAWN TO HIM
MAGICALLY ♪

31:08.533 --> 31:11.578
♪ AND THROUGH EVERY MOMENT
OF TURMOIL ♪

31:11.661 --> 31:14.622
♪ AND MOMENT OF PAIN ♪

31:14.706 --> 31:17.417
♪ THROUGH ALL
OF OUR MISADVENTURES ♪

31:17.500 --> 31:21.129
♪ ONE THING REMAINS ♪

31:21.212 --> 31:23.965
♪ FACING PIXIES, BULLIES,
AND JAR-HEADS ♪

31:24.048 --> 31:27.302
♪ I'LL NEVER BE BLUE ♪

31:27.385 --> 31:35.310
♪ AS LONG AS
I'M FLOATING WITH YOU ♪

31:35.393 --> 31:38.354
{\an1}Cosmo: ♪ I SAW HER
AND NO OTHER ♪

31:38.438 --> 31:41.316
♪ I STILL LIVED WITH MY MOTHER ♪

31:41.399 --> 31:46.904
{\an1}♪ WHEN I SPOTTED
HER SWIRLY PINK HAIR ♪

31:46.988 --> 31:51.159
{\an1}♪ THOUGH MY SHOES
SMELL LIKE TAR PITS ♪

31:51.242 --> 31:53.119
♪ AND I DON'T WASH MY ARMPITS ♪

31:53.202 --> 32:00.543
{\an1}♪ I LIKE MONKEYS TOO MUCH,
BUT I KNOW SHE DOESN'T CARE ♪

32:00.627 --> 32:03.838
♪ AND I KNOW
THAT I'M FORGETFUL ♪

32:03.921 --> 32:07.175
♪ I KNOW I'M DIM ♪

32:07.258 --> 32:09.636
♪ AND EVEN THOUGH
I'VE JUST EATEN ♪

32:09.719 --> 32:13.222
♪ I KNOW I'LL SWIM ♪

32:13.306 --> 32:16.225
{\an8}♪ I KNOW
THAT IT DOESN'T MATTER ♪

32:16.309 --> 32:19.228
♪ IF I CAN'T COUNT TO 2 ♪

32:19.312 --> 32:25.485
♪ AS LONG AS
I'M FLOATING WITH YOU ♪

32:35.119 --> 32:38.331
{\an1}Together: ♪ EVEN THOUGH
WE'RE IN DEEP HERE ♪

32:38.414 --> 32:41.417
{\an1}♪ AND THEY MIGHT
MAKE US SLEEP HERE ♪

32:41.501 --> 32:43.419
♪ HERE WITH YOU, DEAR ♪

32:43.503 --> 32:47.715
{\an1}♪ IS WHERE WE BOTH
MAKE OUR STAND ♪

32:47.799 --> 32:50.885
♪ I AM BRACED
FOR ATTACK AND ♪

32:50.968 --> 32:54.055
{\an1}♪ KNOWING SHE
HAS MY BACK END ♪

32:54.138 --> 33:00.478
♪ ALL I NEED
IS HER HAND IN MY HAND ♪

33:00.561 --> 33:02.897
♪ BABY, I KNOW
I CAN BE NAGGING ♪

33:02.980 --> 33:06.984
{\an1}♪ I KNOW
YOU'RE NAGGY, TOO ♪

33:07.068 --> 33:09.529
♪ I KNOW THAT
I'M DEMANDING ♪

33:09.612 --> 33:11.406
{\an1}♪ OH, MAN,
IS THAT TRUE! ♪

33:13.116 --> 33:16.160
{\an1}♪ BUT ONE THING
I'M UNDERSTANDING ♪

33:16.244 --> 33:18.788
♪ NO MATTER
WHAT WE GO THROUGH ♪

33:18.871 --> 33:21.999
♪ I'D RATHER GO THROUGH IT ♪

33:22.083 --> 33:25.920
♪ I KNOW
I'LL GET THROUGH IT ♪

33:26.003 --> 33:34.262
{\an1}♪ IF I'M FLOATING
THROUGH IT WITH YOU ♪

33:40.643 --> 33:42.437
YOU REALLY ARE
KIND OF NAGGY.

33:42.520 --> 33:43.938
{\an1}DID YOU GET
THE HANDCUFF KEY?

33:44.021 --> 33:45.606
YEP. OPERATION
DISTRACT JORGEN

33:45.690 --> 33:48.109
{\an5}WITH A STUPID
GOOEY LOVE SONG
WORKS EVERY TIME.

33:48.192 --> 33:48.860
{\an1}[CRYING]

33:48.943 --> 33:51.779
"I SAW HER AND NO OTHER"...

33:51.863 --> 33:53.823
{\an1}OH, AND THAT PART
WITH THE FINGERPRINTS!

33:53.906 --> 33:57.118
{\an1}FINGERS AREN'T
SHAPED LIKE THAT!

33:57.201 --> 33:58.745
THAT IS LOVE!

33:58.828 --> 33:59.620
{\an1}[CRYING]

33:59.704 --> 34:02.373
COME ON. WE'VE GOT TO
GET DOWN TO EARTH!

34:04.208 --> 34:07.920
WELL, H.P., NOW THAT
FLAPPY HAS GIVEN US

34:08.004 --> 34:10.005
TOTAL CONTROL
OVER FAIRY WORLD,

34:10.089 --> 34:10.715
WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO DO WITH IT?

34:10.797 --> 34:12.925
{\an1}I'M THINKING
DULL AND GRAY.

34:13.009 --> 34:15.762
I WAS THINKING
GRAY AND DULL,

34:15.844 --> 34:17.764
BUT THAT'S WHY
YOU'RE THE BOSS.

34:17.847 --> 34:19.306
[RINGING]

34:21.516 --> 34:23.311
[SCREAMING]

34:28.900 --> 34:30.275
DID YOU HEAR
THE ONE ABOUT...

34:32.235 --> 34:34.237
AAH, PIXIE MAGIC.

34:34.322 --> 34:35.406
IT'S SUCKING AWAY
ALL THE FUN!

34:38.284 --> 34:40.161
OH, WE'RE NEVER
GONNA MAKE IT!

34:40.244 --> 34:42.663
{\an1}THERE'S STILL ENOUGH
PRETTY COLOR LEFT

34:42.746 --> 34:44.331
{\an1}FOR ONE OF US TO SLIDE DOWN
THE RAINBOW BRIDGE.

34:44.415 --> 34:48.418
{\an4}WOW. THERE WASN'T
A MANLY WORD
IN THAT SENTENCE.

34:48.503 --> 34:49.962
WE NEED A MAGIC WAND.

34:50.045 --> 34:52.172
OH, NO. PIXIE MAGIC.

34:52.255 --> 34:53.341
[GASPING]

34:53.424 --> 34:57.011
I STILL HAVE MY WAND.
MAYBE I CAN STOP THIS!

34:59.305 --> 35:01.015
AAH! NO!

35:01.098 --> 35:01.307
AAH!

35:05.728 --> 35:08.564
OH, COSMO.

35:10.107 --> 35:11.526
GO!

35:11.609 --> 35:13.236
AAH!

35:13.319 --> 35:15.071
WANDA!

35:15.154 --> 35:17.698
COSMO!

35:17.782 --> 35:18.658
WHEE!

35:18.741 --> 35:21.327
COSMO!

35:24.163 --> 35:26.207
COSMO!

35:26.290 --> 35:27.250
I AM NOT NAGGY!

35:34.465 --> 35:35.675
THIS STINKS!

35:35.758 --> 35:37.718
{\an1}WE CAN'T FLOAT.
WE CAN'T DO MAGIC.

35:37.802 --> 35:40.179
{\an1}AND THIS SUIT--
I CAN'T WEAR GRAY.

35:40.263 --> 35:42.431
I'M A FAIRY!

35:42.515 --> 35:44.517
BINKY, NO!

35:44.600 --> 35:45.852
AAH!

35:46.519 --> 35:48.813
LOOK AT ME.
I'M COLORFUL.

35:48.896 --> 35:50.690
COLORFUL!

35:50.773 --> 35:51.566
AAH!

35:51.649 --> 35:53.401
[RINGING]

35:57.905 --> 36:00.533
[CRACKING KNUCKLES]

36:05.746 --> 36:06.414
♪ THIS USED TO BE A FUN PLACE ♪

36:06.497 --> 36:07.748
♪ BUT NOW WE WEAR A SAD FACE ♪

36:07.832 --> 36:11.502
{\an1}♪ SINCE PIXIES HAVE ALL REPLACED
THE WAY THAT THINGS ARE DONE ♪

36:11.586 --> 36:12.253
♪ THERE'S NO MORE
GRANTING WISHES ♪

36:12.336 --> 36:14.505
{\an1}♪ YOU CAN'T TURN
INTO FISHES ♪

36:14.589 --> 36:15.923
♪ NOW PIPE DOWN,
DO THE DISHES ♪

36:16.007 --> 36:17.425
{\an1}♪ COME ON, NOW,
EVERYONE ♪

36:17.508 --> 36:20.595
{\an1}♪ THESE ARE THE UNFUNDAMENTALS
FOR US FAIRY GODPARENTALS ♪

36:20.678 --> 36:23.306
♪ WHO ARE NOW DEVOID OF WISHING
AND OF MIRTH ♪

36:23.389 --> 36:25.391
♪ WE'RE CERTIFIABLY DE-MENTAL
'CAUSE THESE UNFUNDAMENTALS ♪

36:25.474 --> 36:29.604
♪ MAKE BEING A FAIRY
ABOUT AS FUN AS GIVING BIRTH ♪

36:29.687 --> 36:31.898
{\an1}♪ I'LL BET IT'S EVEN WORSE
DOWN THERE ON EARTH ♪

36:31.981 --> 36:34.650
Wanda: TIMMY? TIMMY?

36:36.068 --> 36:37.528
TIMMY! TIMMY?

36:37.612 --> 36:39.906
TIMMY?

36:39.989 --> 36:42.909
{\an1}♪ ALL THE ARCADES
NOW CLOSE AT 3:00 ♪

36:42.992 --> 36:45.953
♪ THE TRAMPOLINES
ARE BOUNCY-FREE ♪

36:46.037 --> 36:48.164
{\an1}♪ AND THERE'S A PAD
ON EVERY KNEE ♪

36:48.247 --> 36:51.959
{\an1}♪ EVERYTHING'S FINE
FAR AS I SEE ♪

36:52.043 --> 36:55.129
{\an1}♪ BUT I CAN'T HELP
BUT THINK OUT LOUD ♪

36:55.212 --> 36:58.049
{\an1}♪ THE THINGS THAT KID
HAD SAID SOMEHOW ♪

36:58.132 --> 37:01.052
{\an1}♪ MY MOM AND DAD
WOULD NOT BE PROUD ♪

37:01.135 --> 37:04.055
{\an1}♪ OF THE PATH
I'VE TAKEN IN LIFE ♪

37:04.138 --> 37:07.099
♪ HAVE I BEEN WRONG?
HAVE I BEEN USED? ♪

37:07.183 --> 37:10.394
{\an1}♪ SHOULD I EMBRACE
MY NOSE AND SHOES? ♪

37:10.478 --> 37:13.856
{\an1}♪ ACCEPT THESE GIFTS
I ONCE REFUSED ♪

37:13.940 --> 37:15.858
♪ I'M HAPPY PEPPY-- ♪

37:15.942 --> 37:17.985
NOT NOW!

37:18.069 --> 37:19.904
♪ OUR HEADS MUST BE PROTECTED ♪

37:19.987 --> 37:20.696
♪ OUR BODIES DISINFECTED ♪

37:20.780 --> 37:22.406
♪ THIS IS JUST AS I SUSPECTED ♪

37:22.490 --> 37:23.449
{\an1}♪ WHAT WOULD HAPPEN IF THIS
WORLD WAS RULED BY... ♪

37:23.532 --> 37:26.869
♪ UNFUNDAMENTALS,
SURELY ALL YOU PARENTALS ♪

37:26.953 --> 37:29.705
{\an1}♪ MUST SEE HOW DEVOID OF FUN
THIS TRULY, TRULY IS ♪

37:29.789 --> 37:31.415
♪ BUT ALL THESE
UNFUNDAMENTALS ♪

37:31.499 --> 37:33.167
♪ SEEM QUITE INSTRUMENTAL ♪

37:33.250 --> 37:35.628
♪ TO KEEP ALL OF YOU
ROWDY KIDS IN LINE ♪

37:35.711 --> 37:37.546
♪ IF YOU NEED US,
WE'LL BE PLAYING THE BACK 9 ♪

37:45.346 --> 37:47.848
{\an1}WELL, SANDERSON,
WE'VE DONE IT.

37:47.932 --> 37:49.684
ONE OF
OUR 37-YEAR PLANS

37:49.767 --> 37:51.143
HAS FINALLY
GIVEN US CONTROL

37:51.227 --> 37:52.812
OVER ALL THE MAGIC.

37:52.895 --> 37:55.856
{\an1}YES, H.P., IF THIS PLACE
WERE ANY LESS FUN,

37:55.940 --> 37:57.358
IT WOULD NEED A LIBRARIAN.

37:57.441 --> 37:59.402
[DULL LAUGHING]

38:01.278 --> 38:04.865
{\an1}WELL, FLOPPY SHOES,
BIG RED NOSE,

38:04.949 --> 38:07.201
I GUESS THIS IS GOOD-BYE.

38:07.284 --> 38:09.036
[DULL LAUGHING]

38:09.120 --> 38:12.039
HEY, MY FLOATING
RICH FRIENDS.

38:12.123 --> 38:13.207
AND JUST THINK,

38:13.290 --> 38:15.126
{\an1}ALL WE HAD TO DO TO
BEAT OUR FAIRY ENEMIES

38:15.209 --> 38:17.878
{\an1}WAS RIP
A CLOWN CHILD AWAY

38:17.962 --> 38:19.714
{\an1}FROM HIS
SUPER-HILARIOUS DESTINY

38:19.797 --> 38:22.258
{\an1}AND CONVINCE HIM
THAT FUN WASN'T FUN

38:22.341 --> 38:24.427
AND THAT BORING WAS FUN.

38:24.510 --> 38:28.014
YOU'D HAVE TO BE A CLOWN
TO FALL FOR THAT.

38:28.097 --> 38:30.182
A REALLY DUMB CLOWN.

38:30.266 --> 38:32.435
[DULL LAUGHING]

38:32.518 --> 38:34.520
THAT KID WAS RIGHT!

38:34.603 --> 38:36.022
THEY WERE USING ME!

38:39.191 --> 38:43.320
{\an1}I'LL SHOW THEM
WHO'S A DUMB CLOWN.

38:43.404 --> 38:44.447
[SQUEAKING]

38:48.492 --> 38:51.704
{\an1}UGH. I'M GONNA HAVE TO
DO THIS BY MYSELF.

38:51.787 --> 38:53.748
TIMMY! IT'S HORRIBLE!

38:53.831 --> 38:56.000
{\an1}PIXIES HAVE TAKEN CONTROL
OF FAIRY WORLD!

38:56.083 --> 38:58.586
{\an5}WANDA! WOW,
FOR A QUARTER
OF A SECOND THERE,

38:58.669 --> 38:59.545
I THOUGHT I WAS
IN BIG TROUBLE.

39:01.005 --> 39:03.132
[BEEPING]

39:06.594 --> 39:08.054
[SIREN]

39:10.514 --> 39:12.808
[BEEPING]

39:15.978 --> 39:17.104
THEY'RE NOT LETTING US
DO ANYTHING FUN!

39:17.188 --> 39:20.191
{\an1}I KNOW. LET'S MAKE IT
GO AWAY.

39:20.274 --> 39:23.360
{\an1}I WISH THE WORLD
WAS BACK TO NORMAL!

39:24.653 --> 39:26.447
OH, NO! BECAUSE OF
THAT PIXIE CONTRACT,

39:26.530 --> 39:29.867
{\an5}THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO TO BREAK
THE WISH.

39:29.950 --> 39:31.786
Flappy Bob: I DON'T KNOW
WHO SAID THAT...

39:31.869 --> 39:35.915
{\an1}BUT WITH THE RIGHT AMOUNT
OF FUN, ANYTHING'S POSSIBLE.

39:35.998 --> 39:37.583
FLAPPY BOB?

39:37.666 --> 39:38.751
THAT'S RIGHT.

39:38.834 --> 39:40.127
FLAPPY BOB.

39:40.211 --> 39:42.463
HA HA HA HA! CLOWN!

39:48.094 --> 39:49.845
I WAS A CLOWN AT BIRTH,

39:49.929 --> 39:51.305
BUT THOSE TWO RICH GUYS

39:51.388 --> 39:54.433
RAISED ME TO BE
A BORING BUSINESSMAN.

39:54.517 --> 39:57.144
{\an5}AND IF THERE'S
ONE THING BORING
BUSINESSMEN KNOW,

39:57.228 --> 39:59.522
IT'S HOW
TO FIND A LOOPHOLE.

40:01.607 --> 40:03.234
OH. OH, THAT'S GOOD!

40:03.317 --> 40:06.153
YOU GET THOSE
CONE DOMES DOWN HERE,

40:06.237 --> 40:07.738
AND I'LL DO THE REST.

40:07.822 --> 40:09.990
{\an1}AND THERE'S ONLY
ONE WAY TO DO THAT.

40:10.074 --> 40:12.827
LET'S GET FUN!

40:12.910 --> 40:14.537
I LIKE FUN!

40:14.620 --> 40:17.373
I'M ALL ABOUT
THE FUN NOW!

40:22.795 --> 40:23.587
HA HA HA HA!

40:30.052 --> 40:32.596
{\an8}♪ HEY, FLAPPY BOB,
CAN'T YOU SEE
WHAT THEY'VE DONE? ♪

40:34.807 --> 40:39.186
{\an1}♪ IT MIGHT REEK NOW,
BUT IT CAN ALL BE UNDONE ♪

40:39.270 --> 40:41.355
♪ SO GRAB YOUR KITES
AND WATER GUNS ♪

40:41.438 --> 40:42.148
MY BIKE!

40:41.438 --> 40:42.148
MY CLONE!

40:42.231 --> 40:44.942
THIS BIG STICKY BUN!

40:45.025 --> 40:46.485
♪ IT'S NOT A CRIME ♪

40:46.569 --> 40:48.654
♪ TO HAVE YOUR TIME IN THE SUN ♪

40:50.865 --> 40:53.492
♪ KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

40:53.576 --> 40:56.370
♪ ACTING UP AND EATING DIRT ♪

40:56.453 --> 40:57.705
♪ KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

40:59.790 --> 41:01.417
♪ THEY COULD ALL GET HURT ♪

41:01.500 --> 41:04.420
♪ KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

41:04.503 --> 41:07.047
{\an1}♪ CAN KEEP THOSE GOONS
OFF ALL OUR BUTTS ♪

41:07.131 --> 41:09.383
{\an1}♪ WE'LL GET THIS TOWN
OUT OF ITS RUT ♪

41:09.466 --> 41:12.887
♪ BY US KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

41:12.970 --> 41:15.055
{\an1}♪ YO, WE'RE PIXIES,
WE'RE PIXIES ♪

41:15.139 --> 41:17.391
{\an1}♪ WE FINALLY RULE
ALL THE TRICKS, SEE? ♪

41:17.474 --> 41:19.226
{\an1}♪ THE TIME HAS COME,
THE DEAL'S GONE THROUGH ♪

41:19.310 --> 41:20.227
♪ THERE'S FUN?
STAY THERE ♪

41:20.311 --> 41:20.936
♪ WE'LL COME TO YOU ♪

41:21.020 --> 41:22.438
♪ WE'RE PIXIES, WE'RE PIXIES ♪

41:22.521 --> 41:25.441
{\an1}♪ THIS IS HOW WE GET
OUR KICK-SEES ♪

41:25.524 --> 41:27.443
{\an1}♪ OUR PLAN HAS WORKED,
AND THEY HAVE LOST ♪

41:27.526 --> 41:29.278
♪ LET'S PING ON DOWN
TO SHOW WHO'S THE BOSS ♪

41:29.361 --> 41:31.655
♪ THE PIXIES, THE PIXIES ♪

41:31.739 --> 41:34.158
♪ THE PIXIES ♪

41:36.702 --> 41:38.078
♪ YOU TWO SHOUT
REAL LOUDLY ♪

41:38.162 --> 41:40.247
{\an1}♪ IT'S YOUR TURN
NOW TO ROAR ♪

41:40.331 --> 41:44.251
{\an1}♪ YOU GET TO PARADE PROUDLY
WITH THIS DRUM AND BUGLE CORPS ♪

41:44.335 --> 41:46.128
♪ YOU FIND THE KIDS
AND WOW THEM ♪

41:46.212 --> 41:48.255
♪ I'LL GIVE THEM
WHAT THEY NEED ♪

41:48.339 --> 41:49.673
{\an1}♪ WITH THIS MUCH FUN,
THOSE CONEHEADS ♪

41:49.757 --> 41:51.509
{\an1}♪ SHOULD BE HERE
AT BREAKNECK SPEED ♪

41:51.592 --> 41:53.761
♪ I'D COME THROUGH
WITH EVERYTHING ♪

41:53.844 --> 41:54.553
♪ AT LEAST
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT ♪

41:54.637 --> 41:57.681
{\an1}♪ YOU KIDS RUINED
EVERYTHING ♪

41:57.765 --> 41:58.599
♪ THAT'S THE LIE I BOUGHT ♪

41:58.682 --> 42:01.268
{\an1}♪ BUT SOMEONE ELSE
WAS PULLING STRINGS ♪

42:01.352 --> 42:03.270
♪ AS FAR AS WE COULD TELL ♪

42:03.354 --> 42:06.106
♪ BUT YOU AND ME
CAN SET US FREE ♪

42:06.190 --> 42:10.486
♪ EVERYTHING ENDS WELL ♪

42:22.206 --> 42:24.291
THAT'S QUITE ENOUGH, FLAPPY.

42:24.375 --> 42:26.710
YOU LIED TO ME.

42:26.794 --> 42:29.922
YOU LIED TO ME
FOR 37 YEARS.

42:30.005 --> 42:31.257
YOU TRICKED ME
AND KEPT ME FROM BEING

42:31.340 --> 42:33.300
THE SUPER-HILARIOUS--

42:33.384 --> 42:34.677
IF NOT SOMEWHAT CREEPY--

42:34.760 --> 42:36.762
CLOWN I WAS
DESTINED TO BE!

42:36.845 --> 42:38.305
YES. YES, WE DID.

42:38.389 --> 42:39.473
DUH.

42:39.556 --> 42:40.891
BUT WE HAVE
AN IRONCLAD CONTRACT.

42:44.395 --> 42:45.813
OH, I AGREE.

42:45.896 --> 42:49.233
{\an5}EVERY WORD
IN THIS CONTRACT
IS TOTALLY BINDING,

42:49.316 --> 42:51.777
{\an5}WHICH IS WHY
I'D LIKE TO TURN
YOUR ATTENTION...

42:51.860 --> 42:52.903
TO THIS.

43:00.369 --> 43:04.373
"...AS DEFINED BY FLAPPY BOB."

43:04.456 --> 43:06.834
{\an1}AND GUESS WHAT
I DEFINE AS FUN NOW?

43:06.917 --> 43:11.714
{\an1}EVERYTHING BEING EXACTLY
THE WAY IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE!

43:13.841 --> 43:15.175
OH, SMOOF.

43:15.259 --> 43:15.884
{\an5}YOU KNOW,
YOU PROBABLY
SHOULDN'T

43:15.968 --> 43:16.844
HAVE SENT HIM
TO LAW SCHOOL.

43:16.927 --> 43:19.096
{\an1}YOU MIGHT HAVE THWARTED US
THIS TIME, TURNER,

43:19.179 --> 43:20.597
BUT MARK MY WORDS:

43:20.681 --> 43:24.435
{\an1}OUR NEXT 37-YEAR PLAN
WILL NOT FAIL.

43:24.518 --> 43:27.354
{\an1}WHEN YOU'RE 47,
YOU'LL PAY.

43:27.438 --> 43:29.023
[RINGING]

43:45.122 --> 43:47.166
AH! MY STUPID POINTY HAT!

43:47.249 --> 43:48.083
IT'S A CROWN AGAIN!

43:48.167 --> 43:51.211
AND STILL NOT A MANLY WORD
TO BE FOUND.

43:52.796 --> 43:56.008
{\an1}WOW. THAT WAS
EXTENUATINGLY MANLY.

43:56.091 --> 43:58.635
[CHEERING]

43:58.719 --> 44:01.096
WAY TO GO, FLAPPY.
YOU DID IT!

44:01.180 --> 44:03.724
YOU BROUGHT FUN
BACK TO DIMMSDALE.

44:03.807 --> 44:07.227
{\an5}YEAH. I JUST WISH
MY CLOWN MOTHER
AND CLOWN FATHER

44:07.311 --> 44:08.437
WERE HERE TO SEE THIS.

44:08.520 --> 44:10.606
I'M SURE
WHEREVER THEY ARE,

44:10.689 --> 44:12.274
THEY'RE PROUD.

44:12.358 --> 44:13.233
Man and woman:
WE'RE SO PROUD!

44:13.317 --> 44:14.318
HUH?

44:13.317 --> 44:14.318
HUH?

44:14.401 --> 44:16.528
[HORN HONKING]

44:16.612 --> 44:17.821
{\an1}FLAPPY!

44:16.612 --> 44:17.821
FLAPPY!

44:17.905 --> 44:19.698
WE'VE BEEN LOOKING
EVERYWHERE FOR YOU.

44:19.782 --> 44:23.577
EXCEPT, WELL,
THIS SPOT RIGHT HERE!

44:23.660 --> 44:25.329
{\an1}WE LOOKED EVERYWHERE
THERE COULD BE CLOWNS:

44:25.412 --> 44:27.623
FAST FOOD RESTAURANTS,

44:27.706 --> 44:30.459
THE CIRCUS,
THAT HOTEL IN LAS VEGAS...

44:30.542 --> 44:32.628
{\an1}WE SPENT A LOT
OF TIME IN VEGAS.

44:32.711 --> 44:33.921
{\an1}36 YEARS!

44:34.004 --> 44:35.756
THEY COMPED OUR ROOM!

44:35.839 --> 44:37.758
{\an1}WE EVEN CHECKED
THE U.S. CONGRESS.

44:37.841 --> 44:41.303
{\an1}IT WAS FULL OF CLOWNS,
BUT NONE OF THEM WERE FUN!

44:41.387 --> 44:43.722
MOM! DAD!

44:45.641 --> 44:47.393
{\an4}YAY!

44:45.641 --> 44:47.393
YAY!

44:45.641 --> 44:47.393
YAY!

44:47.476 --> 44:50.396
AND WE'LL NEVER
LOSE YOU AGAIN.

44:50.479 --> 44:51.772
BUT IF WE DO,

44:51.855 --> 44:54.149
{\an1}LET'S ALL AGREE
TO MEET IN VEGAS!

44:54.233 --> 44:56.110
[HONKING]

44:56.193 --> 44:57.611
YOU FOUND
HIS PARENTS FOR HIM?

44:57.694 --> 44:59.279
{\an1}HEY, HE SAID
HE WANTED EVERYTHING

44:59.363 --> 45:01.615
THE WAY IT SHOULD BE.

45:01.698 --> 45:03.117
{\an1}WELL, PIXIES
AREN'T THE ONLY ONES

45:03.200 --> 45:05.285
{\an1}WHO CAN EXPLOIT
A LOOPHOLE, YOU KNOW.

45:05.369 --> 45:08.163
COSMO!

45:08.247 --> 45:09.164
HERE'S
YOUR WAND BACK.

45:09.248 --> 45:11.792
OH, YOU SAVED
THE DAY AND THE FUN,

45:11.875 --> 45:12.459
WHICH IS WEIRD,
BECAUSE NORMALLY

45:12.543 --> 45:14.628
YOU'RE THE ONE
KILLING IT.

45:14.711 --> 45:15.796
STOP IT, COSMO.

45:15.879 --> 45:16.797
SEE?

45:16.880 --> 45:17.965
AND BEST OF ALL,

45:18.048 --> 45:19.341
WITH THE PIXIES
DEFEATED

45:19.425 --> 45:21.009
AND FLAPPY BOB
ON THE PATH TO FUN,

45:21.093 --> 45:24.680
{\an5}THAT MEANS NO MORE
CAMP LEARN-A-TORIUM,
RIGHT?

45:25.722 --> 45:26.932
Gary: HEY THERE,
SPECIAL GUESTS,

45:27.015 --> 45:30.352
WELCOME TO GARY AND BETTY'S
LEARN-A-TORIUM!

45:30.436 --> 45:31.854
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE

45:31.937 --> 45:32.646
THE MOST
FUN-DU-CATIONAL,

45:32.730 --> 45:36.692
EDU-CA-RIFFIC SUMMER
OF YOUR LIVES!

45:36.775 --> 45:38.485
UH, GUYS? FUN TIME?

45:38.569 --> 45:41.655
{\an1}FUN TIME!

45:38.569 --> 45:41.655
FUN TIME!

45:41.739 --> 45:44.533
UH, THIS IS FUN.
I'LL HANDLE IT.

45:53.459 --> 45:55.002
[CHEERING]

45:55.085 --> 45:55.419
♪ MY EARS ♪

45:55.502 --> 45:57.796
♪ MY HEART ♪

45:57.880 --> 45:59.423
{\an1}♪ SOMETHING'S TEARING
OUR WHOLE WORLD APART ♪

45:59.506 --> 46:01.508
♪ HAVE WISH ♪

46:01.592 --> 46:02.843
♪ WILL GRANT ♪

46:02.926 --> 46:04.761
♪ THERE'S NOTHING BORING
THAT WE CAN'T ENCHANT ♪

46:04.845 --> 46:08.182
♪ MY LEGS!
WE SHOULD HAVE KNOWN ♪

46:08.265 --> 46:10.517
{\an1}♪ THEY MADE US PEDAL
ALL THE WAY HOME ♪

46:10.601 --> 46:12.644
{\an1}♪ DOING ALL THE THINGS
WE THOUGHT THEY'D FORGIVE ♪

46:12.728 --> 46:14.313
LIKE STREAK!

46:14.396 --> 46:16.690
{\an1}♪ THE SUMMER'S REALLY FUNNER
IF WE'RE KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

46:17.691 --> 46:21.361
♪ KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

46:21.445 --> 46:24.031
{\an1}♪ RUNNING WILD
AND RUNNING FREE ♪

46:24.114 --> 46:25.657
♪ KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

46:25.741 --> 46:29.203
♪ I THINK WE ALL AGREE ♪

46:29.286 --> 46:30.788
♪ KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

46:30.871 --> 46:34.374
♪ CLOSE YOUR EYES
AND COUNT TO 3 ♪

46:34.458 --> 46:37.002
{\an1}♪ WITH SOME CONTROL
PARENTALLY ♪

46:37.085 --> 46:39.922
♪ AND ANYWHERE'S
THE PLACE TO BE ♪

46:40.005 --> 46:42.382
♪ MY FRIENDS AND FAMILY
NEXT TO ME ♪

46:42.466 --> 46:48.055
♪ WITH THOSE KIDS JUST BEING ♪

46:48.138 --> 46:50.557
♪ KIDS JUST BEING KIDS ♪

46:50.641 --> 46:54.061
{\an1}MAYBE WE SHOULD TRY
A 6-WEEK PLAN NEXT TIME.

